1
00:00:02,043 --> 00:00:03,044
[SOBS]

2
00:00:03,128 --> 00:00:04,129
Liv.

3
00:00:04,713 --> 00:00:06,256
Liv, let me explain.

4
00:00:06,339 --> 00:00:08,299
D-Do you still love her?

5
00:00:08,383 --> 00:00:10,176
Liv, what are you saying? You're my wife.

6
00:00:10,260 --> 00:00:12,804
My question is, do you still love her?

7
00:00:13,680 --> 00:00:18,268
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

8
00:00:18,351 --> 00:00:21,312
Every time you said that
you were mad at her,

9
00:00:21,396 --> 00:00:23,523
that you wanted justice,

10
00:00:23,606 --> 00:00:25,024
what did you do next?

11
00:00:26,568 --> 00:00:30,071
You just kept helping her
over and over again.

12
00:00:30,155 --> 00:00:31,740
With Abby.

13
00:00:31,823 --> 00:00:32,991
With Alex.

14
00:00:34,826 --> 00:00:36,578
No matter how angry I am at Juliana,

15
00:00:36,661 --> 00:00:38,079
you understand why…

16
00:00:38,163 --> 00:00:40,081
why I can't leave them.

17
00:00:40,540 --> 00:00:41,791
What do you want?

18
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:44,794
To just let her be in our lives?

19
00:00:46,713 --> 00:00:48,715
I can't share, Victor.

20
00:00:49,507 --> 00:00:50,633
I can't.

21
00:00:51,342 --> 00:00:52,594
Make a decision.

22
00:00:54,387 --> 00:00:55,764
Is it Juliana…

23
00:00:57,182 --> 00:00:58,308
or me?

24
00:00:59,517 --> 00:01:01,644
I can't do what you want.

25
00:01:01,728 --> 00:01:03,730
You saw what situation they're in,
and Abby.

26
00:01:03,813 --> 00:01:04,856
They need me.

27
00:01:04,939 --> 00:01:07,609
- She's in danger--
- Then choose Juliana!

28
00:01:07,692 --> 00:01:09,736
Liv, come on. I need you!

29
00:01:09,819 --> 00:01:11,112
Victor!

30
00:01:11,196 --> 00:01:14,240
I don't need you to need me.

31
00:01:15,366 --> 00:01:18,495
All I need is for you to love me.

32
00:01:18,912 --> 00:01:20,622
Liv, I love you.

33
00:01:21,372 --> 00:01:23,083
I love you. So much.

34
00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:26,169
And if I had the choice,

35
00:01:26,252 --> 00:01:27,587
I'd choose to leave all of this.

36
00:01:27,670 --> 00:01:29,756
I'd go somewhere far away with you.

37
00:01:29,839 --> 00:01:31,591
But I can't do that yet.

38
00:01:31,674 --> 00:01:34,219
As long as I haven't cleared my name…

39
00:01:37,722 --> 00:01:39,474
I could still be separated from you.

40
00:01:41,226 --> 00:01:43,144
Liv, just hang in there
a little longer, okay?

41
00:01:44,604 --> 00:01:47,315
Just a bit more.
All of this will end soon.

42
00:01:47,398 --> 00:01:54,114
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

43
00:02:06,417 --> 00:02:07,627
[VICTOR] Oh, Olivia.

44
00:02:09,295 --> 00:02:11,131
Perfect, I'm done with cooking.

45
00:02:11,756 --> 00:02:12,757
Hold on.

46
00:02:15,218 --> 00:02:16,511
I'll just call…

47
00:02:16,594 --> 00:02:19,389
I'll just call Abby
so she can eat with us.

48
00:02:19,472 --> 00:02:20,932
[PLATES, UTENSILS CLATTER]

49
00:02:29,607 --> 00:02:30,733
[VICTOR] Abby?

50
00:02:34,654 --> 00:02:35,822
Olivia.

51
00:02:36,447 --> 00:02:38,491
I'm sorry for what happened last night.

52
00:02:39,492 --> 00:02:40,910
Don't remind me of that.

53
00:02:41,661 --> 00:02:43,496
Have you seen a doctor?

54
00:02:46,916 --> 00:02:48,418
No need.

55
00:02:48,501 --> 00:02:49,878
I can handle it.

56
00:02:51,337 --> 00:02:52,589
You can?

57
00:02:52,672 --> 00:02:54,632
But you keep running
to my husband for help.

58
00:02:56,718 --> 00:02:57,802
Olivia.

59
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:01,306
I'm sorry if we're bothering you.

60
00:03:02,348 --> 00:03:03,349
But…

61
00:03:03,433 --> 00:03:06,102
Abby and I will find a place
we can move into.

62
00:03:07,228 --> 00:03:08,688
Do you still love my husband?

63
00:03:08,771 --> 00:03:15,778
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

64
00:03:17,113 --> 00:03:18,156
Yes.

65
00:03:21,159 --> 00:03:22,785
But is that still important…

66
00:03:24,954 --> 00:03:26,831
if he loves you now?

67
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,210
[EXHALES DEEPLY] I've accepted it, Olivia.

68
00:03:32,837 --> 00:03:34,839
I missed my chance.

69
00:03:35,506 --> 00:03:37,133
I let…

70
00:03:40,011 --> 00:03:42,055
a man like your husband out of my grasp.

71
00:03:45,308 --> 00:03:46,768
I guess…
[SNIFFLES]

72
00:03:46,851 --> 00:03:48,186
…it's my karma too.

73
00:03:48,269 --> 00:03:53,524
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

74
00:03:53,608 --> 00:03:56,319
I failed to see Victor's value

75
00:03:56,402 --> 00:03:58,238
when we were still together.

76
00:04:02,825 --> 00:04:04,869
But you have nothing to worry about…

77
00:04:07,247 --> 00:04:08,831
because you're the one he loves.

78
00:04:08,915 --> 00:04:15,922
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

79
00:04:28,059 --> 00:04:31,145
Are you ready?
Do you want us to leave together?

80
00:04:34,274 --> 00:04:35,275
I'll wait for you downstairs.

81
00:04:44,701 --> 00:04:45,743
Abby.

82
00:04:47,578 --> 00:04:48,871
Are you okay?

83
00:04:49,789 --> 00:04:51,916
Thank you for letting us stay, Auntie.

84
00:04:54,294 --> 00:04:55,295
It's fine.

85
00:04:55,962 --> 00:04:57,714
As long as you guys are safe.

86
00:05:08,182 --> 00:05:09,851
Do you need anything else?

87
00:05:10,810 --> 00:05:13,855
When will our family be happy?

88
00:05:13,938 --> 00:05:20,862
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

89
00:05:21,529 --> 00:05:23,656
All this time, I was wishing
for Mommy and Daddy

90
00:05:23,740 --> 00:05:25,408
to get back together.

91
00:05:26,909 --> 00:05:28,286
But not like this.

92
00:05:28,369 --> 00:05:30,330
To see Mommy in pain.

93
00:05:31,039 --> 00:05:36,127
Just because your mom
and dad aren't together

94
00:05:36,794 --> 00:05:38,504
doesn't mean you're no longer a family.

95
00:05:39,964 --> 00:05:43,426
You've seen how your dad
cares for your mom, right?

96
00:05:44,302 --> 00:05:46,304
But you're here now.

97
00:05:47,263 --> 00:05:50,391
And I know Daddy loves you.

98
00:05:50,475 --> 00:05:53,686
I'm sorry for resenting you, Auntie.

99
00:05:55,229 --> 00:05:58,900
But now, you're helping us.

100
00:05:59,984 --> 00:06:03,404
You're letting Daddy help us.

101
00:06:03,863 --> 00:06:05,656
[SOBS]

102
00:06:05,740 --> 00:06:07,158
Thank you, Auntie.

103
00:06:07,658 --> 00:06:11,454
[SOBS, SNIFFLES]

104
00:06:11,537 --> 00:06:18,628
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

105
00:06:21,964 --> 00:06:26,969
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

106
00:06:27,970 --> 00:06:29,847
You got involved in their mess?!

107
00:06:31,099 --> 00:06:32,892
I can't just neglect them.

108
00:06:32,975 --> 00:06:34,685
My daughter was in danger!

109
00:06:35,937 --> 00:06:37,730
You know what, I don't care

110
00:06:37,814 --> 00:06:39,565
if you get involved with them.

111
00:06:39,649 --> 00:06:42,902
But you better not protect
the one who killed my daughter!

112
00:06:43,861 --> 00:06:45,905
Juliana already confessed.

113
00:06:45,988 --> 00:06:48,699
She admitted that Alex
made her lie to the police at the time.

114
00:06:48,783 --> 00:06:50,034
And you trust her?

115
00:06:50,493 --> 00:06:51,869
[DANTE SCOFFS]

116
00:06:51,953 --> 00:06:55,540
How can you trust someone
who cheated on you?!

117
00:06:55,623 --> 00:06:57,208
What if they're just manipulating you?

118
00:06:57,291 --> 00:06:58,876
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

119
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:01,129
That's why I've been trying
to gain Juliana's trust.

120
00:07:01,212 --> 00:07:04,048
And she finally confessed
that Alex killed Sylvia.

121
00:07:05,383 --> 00:07:06,676
[DANTE] All right.

122
00:07:06,759 --> 00:07:10,513
Just make sure that the person you trust

123
00:07:10,596 --> 00:07:15,226
isn't working with Alex to manipulate you!

124
00:07:15,309 --> 00:07:21,315
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

125
00:07:21,399 --> 00:07:22,358
[ENGINE STARTS]

126
00:07:26,028 --> 00:07:33,035
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

127
00:08:05,359 --> 00:08:08,112
How long will Juliana stay at your house?

128
00:08:09,405 --> 00:08:11,157
Until everything's settled.

129
00:08:12,366 --> 00:08:13,910
Until everything's settled?

130
00:08:13,993 --> 00:08:15,495
When will that be?

131
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:17,330
[JIMBOY] Hold on.
Let me get this straight.

132
00:08:17,413 --> 00:08:18,873
So, the three of you

133
00:08:18,956 --> 00:08:20,791
are living under one roof?

134
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:22,126
Like one big happy family?

135
00:08:23,794 --> 00:08:26,797
You know, this will all be over

136
00:08:26,881 --> 00:08:29,634
once Victor brings Alex to justice.

137
00:08:29,717 --> 00:08:30,885
That's the only reason

138
00:08:30,968 --> 00:08:33,971
why he's letting Juliana come near him.

139
00:08:34,055 --> 00:08:35,097
Right?

140
00:08:35,181 --> 00:08:39,852
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

141
00:08:43,523 --> 00:08:44,440
[VICTOR EXHALES DEEPLY]

142
00:08:44,524 --> 00:08:46,150
Liv.

143
00:08:46,234 --> 00:08:47,568
Can we talk?

144
00:08:47,652 --> 00:08:49,487
Can we just talk when I get back later?

145
00:08:49,570 --> 00:08:50,821
Where are you going?

146
00:08:50,905 --> 00:08:52,490
I just have to take care of something.

147
00:08:53,824 --> 00:08:55,326
I'll just wait here.

148
00:09:07,964 --> 00:09:10,049
We'll fix all of this when I get back.

149
00:09:11,259 --> 00:09:12,885
Okay?

150
00:09:12,969 --> 00:09:17,974
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

151
00:09:18,057 --> 00:09:19,141
Thank you.

152
00:09:22,353 --> 00:09:23,437
And…

153
00:09:24,647 --> 00:09:26,232
I'm really sorry…

154
00:09:27,942 --> 00:09:29,735
for putting you in this situation.

155
00:09:30,945 --> 00:09:32,863
Everything I do…

156
00:09:36,450 --> 00:09:37,910
is out of my love for you.

157
00:09:37,994 --> 00:09:39,996
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

158
00:09:40,079 --> 00:09:41,622
After this…

159
00:09:43,082 --> 00:09:44,125
I promise…

160
00:09:46,502 --> 00:09:49,463
we'll start our own family.

161
00:09:52,216 --> 00:09:54,218
We can live in peace.

162
00:09:56,178 --> 00:09:59,098
And I will do everything

163
00:09:59,932 --> 00:10:02,351
to make that happen for you, Victor.

164
00:10:03,728 --> 00:10:06,314
I love you so much.

165
00:10:06,397 --> 00:10:12,194
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

166
00:10:12,278 --> 00:10:13,946
I love you too, Liv.

167
00:10:28,919 --> 00:10:35,926
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

168
00:10:50,941 --> 00:10:55,696
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

169
00:10:58,699 --> 00:11:05,706
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

170
00:11:20,721 --> 00:11:27,645
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

171
00:11:34,819 --> 00:11:35,986
[ALEX] Olivia.

172
00:11:38,197 --> 00:11:39,490
Oh.

173
00:11:39,573 --> 00:11:42,535
Sorry, the gate was open
so I just walked in.

174
00:11:43,119 --> 00:11:44,662
What are you doing here?

175
00:11:45,329 --> 00:11:47,498
I've thought about what you said…

176
00:11:48,707 --> 00:11:50,626
about Victor and Juliana.

177
00:11:52,420 --> 00:11:54,713
I think they really are in a relationship.

178
00:11:55,756 --> 00:11:56,799
Really?

179
00:11:57,550 --> 00:11:59,218
Did Victor finally confess?

180
00:12:01,053 --> 00:12:02,805
I didn't have to ask him.

181
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:04,849
I can sense it.

182
00:12:07,143 --> 00:12:08,936
So, what are you planning to do?

183
00:12:10,688 --> 00:12:12,898
Give them what they deserve.

184
00:12:14,733 --> 00:12:15,901
I need your help.

185
00:12:17,069 --> 00:12:19,238
You have to tell me
where Juliana is first.

186
00:12:19,321 --> 00:12:26,328
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

187
00:12:30,583 --> 00:12:32,501
I don't know where she is, but…

188
00:12:34,295 --> 00:12:35,838
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

189
00:12:35,921 --> 00:12:38,841
But I can try to find out from Victor.

190
00:12:39,717 --> 00:12:40,843
On one condition.

191
00:12:42,636 --> 00:12:43,721
What is it?

192
00:12:45,264 --> 00:12:47,308
Tell me. Did you really beat up Juliana?

193
00:12:51,061 --> 00:12:53,522
Beating up is different from reining in.

194
00:12:53,606 --> 00:12:55,983
Is that what you also did to Sylvia?

195
00:12:56,066 --> 00:12:57,902
Why are you bringing up Sylvia?

196
00:13:00,404 --> 00:13:02,740
Since we'll be allies from now on,

197
00:13:02,823 --> 00:13:04,492
you have to be honest with me.

198
00:13:05,451 --> 00:13:08,537
Did you have anything to do with
your late wife's death?

199
00:13:09,622 --> 00:13:11,207
Do you really want to know?

200
00:13:13,334 --> 00:13:15,252
Let's talk about it in detail.

201
00:13:16,670 --> 00:13:17,963
Right here, right now.

202
00:13:18,672 --> 00:13:20,132
Alex, I have to go.

203
00:13:20,799 --> 00:13:21,842
Olivia.

204
00:13:24,011 --> 00:13:25,638
You want to take revenge, right?

205
00:13:27,223 --> 00:13:29,433
I want to get back at them this way.

206
00:13:30,309 --> 00:13:31,727
- Alex.
- [CAR HORN HONKING]

207
00:13:35,731 --> 00:13:37,399
Just stay here. Don't go anywhere.

208
00:13:39,401 --> 00:13:41,320
[PILAR] Victor, thank you for your help.

209
00:13:43,822 --> 00:13:45,157
Don't mention it, Grandma.

210
00:13:48,869 --> 00:13:50,079
What about you, Grandma?

211
00:13:50,162 --> 00:13:51,747
How are you doing?

212
00:13:51,830 --> 00:13:54,583
- How are you and--
- Don't worry about us.

213
00:13:55,125 --> 00:13:56,502
We're doing fine.

214
00:13:56,585 --> 00:14:01,549
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

215
00:14:01,632 --> 00:14:02,675
What about you, Kate?

216
00:14:03,259 --> 00:14:04,301
Are you two back together?

217
00:14:04,385 --> 00:14:06,345
We'll try to start again.

218
00:14:07,304 --> 00:14:08,597
That's right, dear.

219
00:14:09,807 --> 00:14:13,060
If you really love each other,
then fight for it.

220
00:14:14,353 --> 00:14:19,358
It's better to get hurt again
because of a failed relationship

221
00:14:19,441 --> 00:14:22,486
than to live a life full of regrets

222
00:14:22,570 --> 00:14:24,029
because you didn't try to work things out.

223
00:14:24,113 --> 00:14:27,074
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

224
00:14:27,157 --> 00:14:28,325
Grandma.

225
00:14:37,251 --> 00:14:38,711
What are you doing here?

226
00:14:38,794 --> 00:14:41,005
I just wanted to check on Juliana.

227
00:14:41,088 --> 00:14:46,427
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

228
00:14:46,510 --> 00:14:47,344
Oh my God.

229
00:14:48,888 --> 00:14:51,432
I didn't know Alex could do this to you.

230
00:14:54,643 --> 00:14:57,855
I'm really sorry
for everything he has done.

231
00:14:58,689 --> 00:14:59,648
- Amelia.
- Grandma.

232
00:14:59,732 --> 00:15:02,443
Don't apologize for your son!

233
00:15:03,819 --> 00:15:05,112
He can think for himself.

234
00:15:06,238 --> 00:15:09,491
If he was able to beat up
my granddaughter like this,

235
00:15:09,575 --> 00:15:12,578
I'm sure he can come here
to ask for forgiveness.

236
00:15:14,538 --> 00:15:17,333
I never thought we'd reach this point.

237
00:15:18,542 --> 00:15:20,044
Is that all you can do?

238
00:15:22,087 --> 00:15:25,382
Will you just keep blaming yourself
for Alex's mistakes?

239
00:15:26,175 --> 00:15:27,468
If you're only here to do that,

240
00:15:27,551 --> 00:15:28,594
then just leave.

241
00:15:28,677 --> 00:15:30,346
What do you want me to do?

242
00:15:30,429 --> 00:15:33,682
I want to know what happened to Sylvia.

243
00:15:33,766 --> 00:15:36,018
Was it Alex who killed her?

244
00:15:37,436 --> 00:15:39,313
Victor, please. Stop it.

245
00:15:39,396 --> 00:15:41,065
You didn't answer my question.

246
00:15:41,148 --> 00:15:42,608
I don't know!

247
00:15:42,691 --> 00:15:44,568
I really don't know!

248
00:15:44,652 --> 00:15:51,492
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

249
00:15:51,575 --> 00:15:54,286
[AMELIA SOBBING]

250
00:16:15,766 --> 00:16:22,773
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

251
00:16:37,663 --> 00:16:38,706
Victor.

252
00:16:39,415 --> 00:16:41,625
Do you think you can convince Mama?

253
00:16:46,213 --> 00:16:48,924
She's blinded by her love for Alex.

254
00:16:49,883 --> 00:16:52,469
I'm not sure if she can still
distinguish right from wrong.

255
00:16:53,846 --> 00:16:55,764
You should go back inside and rest.

256
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:59,018
You too. Why don't you wait
for Olivia inside?

257
00:17:00,269 --> 00:17:01,895
It's okay. I'll just wait here.

258
00:17:10,279 --> 00:17:14,658
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

259
00:17:14,742 --> 00:17:15,701
Victor!

260
00:17:16,368 --> 00:17:17,369
Look what you've done!

261
00:17:22,666 --> 00:17:23,917
What's going on?

262
00:17:26,795 --> 00:17:29,590
You helped the person
who killed my daughter!

263
00:17:29,673 --> 00:17:33,218
Juliana was at the crime scene
when Sylvia died.

264
00:17:35,262 --> 00:17:40,976
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

265
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:43,979
[MATTEO] It seems he already
saw the message.

266
00:17:45,481 --> 00:17:47,024
I bet he's watched the video.

267
00:17:47,107 --> 00:17:48,734
[LAUGHING]

268
00:17:51,445 --> 00:17:55,282
Victor will regret helping Juliana.

269
00:17:57,951 --> 00:17:59,328
I wonder what he'll do now

270
00:18:01,705 --> 00:18:04,666
that the prime suspect in
Sylvia's murder is Juliana.

271
00:18:04,750 --> 00:18:06,543
The person he saved

272
00:18:07,461 --> 00:18:09,797
is also the very cause of his suffering.

273
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:10,923
[CHUCKLES]

274
00:18:11,006 --> 00:18:12,966
[LAUGHING]

275
00:18:13,050 --> 00:18:15,094
My goodness, Alex.

276
00:18:15,177 --> 00:18:16,470
You really are

277
00:18:17,638 --> 00:18:18,722
something else!

278
00:18:21,475 --> 00:18:23,560
But my question is…

279
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:28,190
Do you think Victor will file
a case against Juliana?

280
00:18:28,732 --> 00:18:29,733
I hope so.

281
00:18:30,484 --> 00:18:32,236
That way, she'll eventually
come crawling back to me.

282
00:18:32,319 --> 00:18:33,862
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

283
00:18:34,446 --> 00:18:37,699
Gather all the evidence
from Sylvia's murder

284
00:18:37,783 --> 00:18:39,701
and plant it on Juliana.

285
00:18:40,869 --> 00:18:43,247
Do everything to make sure
she ends up in jail.

286
00:18:44,039 --> 00:18:45,165
[MATTEO] Copy.

287
00:18:45,249 --> 00:18:47,793
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

288
00:18:47,876 --> 00:18:48,877
Olivia?

289
00:18:49,503 --> 00:18:50,796
Olivia!

290
00:18:50,879 --> 00:18:57,302
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

291
00:18:57,386 --> 00:18:58,428
[ALEX] Olivia!

292
00:18:59,847 --> 00:19:00,931
Matteo, go after her!

293
00:19:07,396 --> 00:19:13,986
- [ENGINE REVVING]
- [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

294
00:19:14,069 --> 00:19:15,070
[TIRES SCREECH]

295
00:19:18,490 --> 00:19:19,491
Olivia!

296
00:19:20,742 --> 00:19:22,161
[PANTING]

297
00:19:22,244 --> 00:19:23,245
Just…

298
00:19:24,246 --> 00:19:26,915
Just calm down, okay?
We just want to talk to you.

299
00:19:26,999 --> 00:19:34,006
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

300
00:19:43,724 --> 00:19:44,808
Olivia!

301
00:19:49,229 --> 00:19:53,817
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

302
00:19:53,901 --> 00:19:55,777
[GRUNTS, GASPS]

303
00:19:57,321 --> 00:19:58,155
[PANTING]

304
00:19:58,238 --> 00:19:59,531
- [MATTEO] Olivia!
- Aah!

305
00:19:59,615 --> 00:20:01,158
[GRUNTS]

306
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:04,453
Olivia, please!

307
00:20:04,536 --> 00:20:06,914
[PANTING]

308
00:20:09,249 --> 00:20:13,879
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

309
00:20:13,962 --> 00:20:14,671
[ENGINE REVVING]

310
00:20:14,755 --> 00:20:16,048
- Aah!
- [TIRES SCREECH]

311
00:20:16,131 --> 00:20:18,342
- [LOUD CRASH]
- [THUDS]

312
00:20:22,554 --> 00:20:29,561
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

313
00:20:34,524 --> 00:20:37,486
What did you do? I thought
we were just going to talk to her!

314
00:20:37,569 --> 00:20:38,445
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

315
00:20:38,528 --> 00:20:41,114
I didn't mean to run her over,
but she suddenly ran in front of me.

316
00:20:41,198 --> 00:20:44,910
[GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

317
00:20:44,993 --> 00:20:45,994
Come on.

318
00:20:47,663 --> 00:20:49,748
We need to take her to a hospital!

319
00:20:51,625 --> 00:20:52,793
We can't help her.

320
00:20:52,876 --> 00:20:54,670
She heard what we did to Sylvia.

321
00:20:54,753 --> 00:20:56,046
She'll rat us out to the cops.

322
00:20:56,129 --> 00:20:57,130
We'll go to jail.

323
00:20:57,214 --> 00:20:59,132
So we're just going to let her die?!

324
00:20:59,216 --> 00:21:00,175
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

325
00:21:00,259 --> 00:21:01,301
Alex.

326
00:21:02,511 --> 00:21:03,804
Please.

327
00:21:03,887 --> 00:21:06,306
Let's not make things worse.

328
00:21:07,224 --> 00:21:08,892
We take her to a hospital.

329
00:21:10,018 --> 00:21:11,436
We'll get away with this.

330
00:21:12,646 --> 00:21:18,360
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

331
00:21:18,443 --> 00:21:21,071
Please tell me I didn't make
a mistake by helping you.

332
00:21:23,949 --> 00:21:28,870
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

333
00:21:28,954 --> 00:21:30,330
That video is real.

334
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:35,168
But I wasn't the one
who killed Sylvia, Victor.

335
00:21:35,252 --> 00:21:36,420
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

336
00:21:36,503 --> 00:21:38,547
As shown in the video,
I went to Alex's house,

337
00:21:38,630 --> 00:21:40,465
but I left shortly afterward.

338
00:21:41,091 --> 00:21:43,885
Abby called to ask where I was.

339
00:21:43,969 --> 00:21:46,847
You even threatened to take
my daughter away, remember?

340
00:21:46,930 --> 00:21:49,725
That's why I left in a hurry!
I swear, I didn't kill Sylvia!

341
00:21:51,101 --> 00:21:53,478
Whoever sent you that video

342
00:21:54,396 --> 00:21:57,065
just wants to trick you
into thinking that I'm the culprit.

343
00:21:57,149 --> 00:21:58,108
But it really wasn't me!

344
00:21:58,191 --> 00:21:59,818
Damn it, Juliana!

345
00:21:59,901 --> 00:22:01,778
What else are you hiding from me?!

346
00:22:03,030 --> 00:22:04,990
Do you really think
I can still trust you?!

347
00:22:05,866 --> 00:22:07,868
[DANTE] How could you do this
to my daughter?!

348
00:22:08,368 --> 00:22:10,996
She treated you like family! More than me!

349
00:22:11,913 --> 00:22:15,292
But you conspired with Alex
to kill my daughter!

350
00:22:15,375 --> 00:22:17,336
Yes, I did something wrong.

351
00:22:17,878 --> 00:22:19,588
I fooled Sylvia.

352
00:22:19,671 --> 00:22:21,965
I hurt her and stole her husband.

353
00:22:22,758 --> 00:22:26,136
But that's all I'm going to apologize for.

354
00:22:27,095 --> 00:22:30,515
Because it never even crossed
my mind to kill Sylvia.

355
00:22:31,558 --> 00:22:33,310
My conscience is clear.

356
00:22:33,393 --> 00:22:34,644
I wasn't the one who killed Sylvia.

357
00:22:34,728 --> 00:22:37,230
Victor, please believe me!

358
00:22:37,689 --> 00:22:39,858
It wasn't me! I had nothing to do with it!

359
00:22:39,941 --> 00:22:41,651
I'm telling you the truth!

360
00:22:41,735 --> 00:22:43,403
Tell that to the police.

361
00:22:43,487 --> 00:22:47,282
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

362
00:22:47,365 --> 00:22:48,075
[LINE RINGING]

363
00:22:48,158 --> 00:22:49,076
Chief.

364
00:22:49,868 --> 00:22:54,164
I have something to report
about my daughter's death.

365
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:01,463
In your first statement,

366
00:23:01,546 --> 00:23:04,508
you said you were with Alex Lualhati.

367
00:23:04,925 --> 00:23:07,886
Now, you're saying he went to Sylvia.

368
00:23:07,969 --> 00:23:09,346
And you followed him.

369
00:23:09,429 --> 00:23:12,015
But you changed your mind,
so you went home.

370
00:23:12,099 --> 00:23:13,433
What really happened?

371
00:23:14,476 --> 00:23:17,687
Sir, everything I'm telling you
right now is true.

372
00:23:17,771 --> 00:23:19,689
Please believe me.

373
00:23:20,732 --> 00:23:22,400
Why did you lie back then?

374
00:23:22,776 --> 00:23:25,779
Don't you know that
lying to the cops is a crime?

375
00:23:25,862 --> 00:23:28,156
You can get jailed for what you did.

376
00:23:28,240 --> 00:23:30,867
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

377
00:23:30,951 --> 00:23:32,911
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

378
00:23:32,994 --> 00:23:34,538
That's the only thing I kept from you.

379
00:23:34,621 --> 00:23:37,124
Please believe me. That's all.

380
00:23:37,207 --> 00:23:39,334
I had nothing to do with Sylvia's death.

381
00:23:39,417 --> 00:23:41,294
And I can't get jailed.

382
00:23:41,378 --> 00:23:43,046
My daughter is waiting for me.

383
00:23:43,713 --> 00:23:46,007
Well then, tell us everything you know

384
00:23:46,091 --> 00:23:48,426
about the death of Sylvia Lualhati.

385
00:23:48,510 --> 00:23:50,095
I don't know anything!

386
00:23:50,178 --> 00:23:51,847
Nothing! I had nothing to do with that!

387
00:23:51,930 --> 00:23:52,931
I'm innocent!

388
00:23:53,014 --> 00:23:54,599
Please, believe me!

389
00:23:54,683 --> 00:23:56,268
[OFFICER] Think about it carefully.

390
00:23:56,351 --> 00:23:58,436
Recall all the details
that will be helpful to us.

391
00:23:59,271 --> 00:24:01,398
Just call me when you're ready to talk.

392
00:24:01,731 --> 00:24:03,275
I'm telling the truth!

393
00:24:03,358 --> 00:24:05,902
I'm telling the truth, sir!

394
00:24:05,986 --> 00:24:11,241
- [SOBBING, SNIFFLING]
- [SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

395
00:24:11,324 --> 00:24:12,325
Victor.

396
00:24:13,451 --> 00:24:15,453
Victor, I know you're there.

397
00:24:15,537 --> 00:24:18,123
Victor, please help me. I'm begging you.

398
00:24:19,166 --> 00:24:20,250
[JULIANA] I'm telling the truth.

399
00:24:20,333 --> 00:24:22,919
I had nothing to do with
what happened to Sylvia.

400
00:24:26,298 --> 00:24:28,925
[SNIFFLING, SOBBING]

401
00:24:29,009 --> 00:24:30,343
Abby.

402
00:24:30,427 --> 00:24:31,803
Abby.

403
00:24:32,554 --> 00:24:35,390
I'm sure my daughter will look for me
when she wakes up.

404
00:24:36,725 --> 00:24:38,476
[JULIANA] She shouldn't know I'm here.

405
00:24:38,560 --> 00:24:39,853
She'll worry about me.

406
00:24:40,604 --> 00:24:42,522
Don't tell her I'm here.

407
00:24:42,606 --> 00:24:45,025
I'm begging you. That's all I ask, Victor.

408
00:24:46,651 --> 00:24:53,408
- [SOBBING]
- [SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

409
00:25:05,295 --> 00:25:06,421
Thank you.

410
00:25:11,968 --> 00:25:13,053
Here you go, dear.

411
00:25:13,803 --> 00:25:15,931
Have something warm
to fill up your stomach.

412
00:25:18,850 --> 00:25:19,768
Thank you, Grandma.

413
00:25:19,851 --> 00:25:20,602
[PHONE CHIMES]

414
00:25:28,485 --> 00:25:29,527
Uh…

415
00:25:31,613 --> 00:25:35,283
The lawyer Dylan knows had an emergency,

416
00:25:35,367 --> 00:25:36,993
so he can't come.

417
00:25:37,077 --> 00:25:39,162
How about William?

418
00:25:39,246 --> 00:25:40,622
Did he reply yet?

419
00:25:40,705 --> 00:25:42,082
What did he say?

420
00:25:42,165 --> 00:25:43,541
- Well…
- [JULIANA SNIFFLES]

421
00:25:43,625 --> 00:25:45,252
They don't know any lawyer.

422
00:25:45,877 --> 00:25:46,878
But…

423
00:25:46,962 --> 00:25:49,923
they will try asking at the Public, uh…

424
00:25:50,006 --> 00:25:51,841
Public Attorney's Office.

425
00:25:51,925 --> 00:25:53,885
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

426
00:25:53,969 --> 00:25:55,845
But they can only go there tomorrow.

427
00:25:56,388 --> 00:25:57,472
[SIGHS]

428
00:25:59,015 --> 00:26:00,350
Don't worry.

429
00:26:01,476 --> 00:26:03,728
We'll find a lawyer.

430
00:26:04,646 --> 00:26:05,438
[SOBS]

431
00:26:05,522 --> 00:26:07,399
I didn't do anything, Grandma.

432
00:26:09,276 --> 00:26:11,778
Hold on, I'll follow up with Mosang.

433
00:26:12,946 --> 00:26:14,656
We'll get you a lawyer.

434
00:26:15,490 --> 00:26:18,702
[SOBBING]

435
00:26:18,785 --> 00:26:21,371
You should eat first.
I'll just follow up with Mosang.

436
00:26:22,914 --> 00:26:29,921
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

437
00:26:33,591 --> 00:26:34,592
Sir?

438
00:26:36,886 --> 00:26:39,306
Can I borrow a cell phone?

439
00:26:40,307 --> 00:26:41,308
Um…

440
00:26:44,978 --> 00:26:46,021
[THUDS]

441
00:26:46,730 --> 00:26:53,737
- [GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]
- [BREATHING SHAKILY]

442
00:27:04,664 --> 00:27:08,126
- [LINE RINGING]
- [BREATHING SHAKILY, SNIFFLING]

443
00:27:08,209 --> 00:27:10,962
[PHONE RINGING]

444
00:27:17,135 --> 00:27:18,178
Hello, Alex?

445
00:27:19,679 --> 00:27:20,513
Juliana.

446
00:27:21,765 --> 00:27:22,640
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

447
00:27:22,724 --> 00:27:24,351
Why did you call? What do you need?

448
00:27:27,520 --> 00:27:29,064
I need your help.

449
00:27:29,147 --> 00:27:36,154
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

450
00:27:37,280 --> 00:27:39,366
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

451
00:27:39,449 --> 00:27:40,825
[LINE RINGING]

452
00:27:41,951 --> 00:27:43,703
[BUSY TONE]

453
00:27:48,041 --> 00:27:49,501
[LINE RINGING]

454
00:27:49,584 --> 00:27:51,252
[BUSY TONE]

455
00:27:53,254 --> 00:28:00,178
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

456
00:28:12,690 --> 00:28:14,109
[ALEX GRUNTS]

457
00:28:14,192 --> 00:28:21,157
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

458
00:28:22,450 --> 00:28:24,327
Thank you for your help, Alex.

459
00:28:25,578 --> 00:28:27,205
I'm glad you came.

460
00:28:29,207 --> 00:28:30,667
Why are you thanking me?

461
00:28:31,876 --> 00:28:33,878
It's my duty as your husband.

462
00:28:35,213 --> 00:28:36,423
And besides,

463
00:28:37,257 --> 00:28:39,884
they only brought you there
for questioning.

464
00:28:39,968 --> 00:28:42,721
Victor is still the suspect
in Sylvia's death.

465
00:28:42,804 --> 00:28:44,639
They can't issue an arrest warrant

466
00:28:44,723 --> 00:28:45,765
for the same case

467
00:28:45,849 --> 00:28:48,351
until the jury has passed
a verdict on Victor.

468
00:28:49,477 --> 00:28:51,688
Sylvia's father is just trying
to drive you into a corner.

469
00:28:52,605 --> 00:28:54,149
That's double jeopardy.

470
00:28:54,816 --> 00:28:55,817
Right, Matteo?

471
00:28:57,986 --> 00:28:58,987
Matteo.

472
00:29:00,739 --> 00:29:02,198
Yes, Alex is right.

473
00:29:05,243 --> 00:29:06,578
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

474
00:29:08,705 --> 00:29:09,706
[JULIANA] Hey.

475
00:29:10,915 --> 00:29:12,459
Where did you two come from?

476
00:29:13,001 --> 00:29:20,008
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

477
00:29:20,800 --> 00:29:21,843
Uh…

478
00:29:22,719 --> 00:29:25,054
The car broke down on our way
to the police station.

479
00:29:25,138 --> 00:29:26,931
So, Matteo had to fix the car.

480
00:29:27,557 --> 00:29:34,564
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

481
00:29:38,818 --> 00:29:39,986
Don't worry.

482
00:29:41,070 --> 00:29:42,405
We'll get Abby back.

483
00:29:44,908 --> 00:29:45,909
No need.

484
00:29:46,701 --> 00:29:48,244
Just let her be for now.

485
00:29:50,580 --> 00:29:52,791
I don't want her to be shocked.

486
00:29:52,874 --> 00:29:54,876
The situation right now
is too complicated.

487
00:29:55,251 --> 00:29:56,252
It's your call.

488
00:29:56,878 --> 00:29:58,546
The important thing is you're back.

489
00:29:58,630 --> 00:30:05,595
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

490
00:30:07,514 --> 00:30:09,349
Olivia isn't here yet.

491
00:30:09,432 --> 00:30:11,810
She hasn't been back since she left.

492
00:30:13,144 --> 00:30:14,521
Where could she be?

493
00:30:14,604 --> 00:30:15,814
[AMELIA] What's wrong?

494
00:30:15,897 --> 00:30:17,607
Is Olivia missing?

495
00:30:18,775 --> 00:30:20,193
Have you called her?

496
00:30:20,276 --> 00:30:21,986
I've been trying to call her
for a while now.

497
00:30:22,070 --> 00:30:24,447
The line kept ringing earlier,
but now it won't.

498
00:30:25,698 --> 00:30:27,283
Before she left, she told me that

499
00:30:27,367 --> 00:30:29,077
she needed to take care of something.

500
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:31,830
Did she say what it was? And where?

501
00:30:31,913 --> 00:30:34,582
I think we should report this
to the police.

502
00:30:34,666 --> 00:30:40,505
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

503
00:31:03,361 --> 00:31:04,737
I missed you, hon.

504
00:31:08,491 --> 00:31:10,285
[SMOOCHES]

505
00:31:11,369 --> 00:31:12,537
What's wrong?

506
00:31:23,798 --> 00:31:25,049
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

507
00:31:29,053 --> 00:31:31,139
I just can't believe that…

508
00:31:35,143 --> 00:31:37,812
they're suspecting me of killing Sylvia.

509
00:31:37,896 --> 00:31:41,983
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

510
00:31:42,066 --> 00:31:44,360
Alex, you know I'm innocent.

511
00:31:47,280 --> 00:31:48,281
I know.

512
00:31:50,742 --> 00:31:51,910
Even Victor…

513
00:31:51,993 --> 00:31:53,953
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

514
00:31:54,787 --> 00:31:57,790
…believes I could've done it.

515
00:32:00,043 --> 00:32:02,045
He judged me, Alex.

516
00:32:05,506 --> 00:32:07,717
So that's why you asked me for help.

517
00:32:07,800 --> 00:32:10,094
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

518
00:32:10,178 --> 00:32:12,388
I have nowhere else to go.

519
00:32:13,640 --> 00:32:16,851
I should've realized a long time ago

520
00:32:18,144 --> 00:32:20,271
that you're the only one who's on my side.

521
00:32:21,356 --> 00:32:22,398
That's okay.

522
00:32:22,482 --> 00:32:24,609
What matters is you know the truth now.

523
00:32:25,818 --> 00:32:28,154
I've always been by your side, Juliana.

524
00:32:28,237 --> 00:32:30,073
I've never abandoned you…

525
00:32:30,949 --> 00:32:32,367
ever.

526
00:32:34,243 --> 00:32:37,121
Why did that CCTV footage
suddenly show up, anyway?

527
00:32:37,205 --> 00:32:39,582
How did Judge Dante get his hands on it?

528
00:32:41,209 --> 00:32:42,710
Do you know anything?

529
00:32:42,794 --> 00:32:45,338
Just think of it
as a blessing in disguise.

530
00:32:45,421 --> 00:32:49,050
At least now you realize
we're really meant for each other.

531
00:32:49,926 --> 00:32:51,469
That footage

532
00:32:51,552 --> 00:32:54,389
helped you realize
what Victor really thinks of you.

533
00:32:54,472 --> 00:32:57,141
What exactly happened to Sylvia?

534
00:32:57,225 --> 00:33:00,436
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

535
00:33:00,520 --> 00:33:02,313
I want to leave the past behind, Juliana.

536
00:33:02,397 --> 00:33:04,023
You should too.

537
00:33:06,192 --> 00:33:07,902
Let's forget

538
00:33:08,903 --> 00:33:11,155
all the bad things that happened to us.

539
00:33:13,366 --> 00:33:14,951
Let's start over.

540
00:33:16,703 --> 00:33:17,912
Okay?

541
00:33:17,996 --> 00:33:25,003
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

542
00:33:42,270 --> 00:33:43,980
Has Olivia arrived?

543
00:33:44,063 --> 00:33:46,899
Victor, I've been waiting
for her all night.

544
00:33:46,983 --> 00:33:50,153
She didn't come home.
Did you go to the police?

545
00:33:50,528 --> 00:33:52,530
We've reported it to the police.

546
00:33:52,613 --> 00:33:55,408
They said they'll call
when they have some news.

547
00:33:55,491 --> 00:33:58,161
We've also been going around,
but there's absolutely nothing.

548
00:33:58,244 --> 00:34:00,455
Aren't you going to ask how Juliana is?

549
00:34:02,081 --> 00:34:04,333
You know it's not easy to admit a crime

550
00:34:04,417 --> 00:34:05,918
you didn't commit.

551
00:34:07,045 --> 00:34:09,422
I just want to know the truth, Grandma.

552
00:34:10,048 --> 00:34:12,383
That's the only way to clear my name.

553
00:34:13,342 --> 00:34:15,344
Well, she was released anyway.

554
00:34:17,138 --> 00:34:18,139
How?

555
00:34:18,639 --> 00:34:19,932
Because of Alex.

556
00:34:20,975 --> 00:34:23,895
[BADONG]<i> You know, it's all going to end</i>

557
00:34:23,978 --> 00:34:25,813
<i>once Alex has been held accountable.</i>

558
00:34:26,856 --> 00:34:27,940
<i>That's the only reason</i>

559
00:34:28,024 --> 00:34:30,485
<i>why he lets Juliana come to him.</i>

560
00:34:30,985 --> 00:34:32,320
Right.

561
00:34:32,403 --> 00:34:33,738
It's Alex.

562
00:34:34,864 --> 00:34:36,199
Alex?

563
00:34:36,908 --> 00:34:39,035
I told Olivia

564
00:34:39,118 --> 00:34:41,079
that all of this would only end

565
00:34:41,788 --> 00:34:44,082
once Alex paid for his sins.

566
00:34:44,165 --> 00:34:46,209
Once you cleared your name.

567
00:34:47,585 --> 00:34:49,712
Could it be that she went to see Alex?

568
00:34:49,796 --> 00:34:53,883
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

569
00:34:53,966 --> 00:34:55,051
Alex!

570
00:34:57,095 --> 00:35:00,056
What are you doing here?
Leave Juliana and me alone.

571
00:35:01,641 --> 00:35:02,892
[JULIANA] Alex.

572
00:35:03,601 --> 00:35:05,645
I didn't come here for Juliana.

573
00:35:07,396 --> 00:35:08,481
Where is Olivia?

574
00:35:08,564 --> 00:35:10,274
Why are you asking me?

575
00:35:10,733 --> 00:35:13,486
Olivia is missing. We can't contact her.

576
00:35:13,569 --> 00:35:15,863
Someone told me
that she might have come here.

577
00:35:18,407 --> 00:35:20,076
She's not here.

578
00:35:20,159 --> 00:35:21,869
Besides, why would she come here?

579
00:35:24,163 --> 00:35:26,541
Ah, I know.

580
00:35:26,624 --> 00:35:28,626
Maybe she hit her head

581
00:35:28,709 --> 00:35:31,087
and she realized
what kind of person you truly are.

582
00:35:31,170 --> 00:35:32,672
So she left you.

583
00:35:32,755 --> 00:35:34,465
Olivia wouldn't do that.

584
00:35:35,967 --> 00:35:37,552
If that's the case, then…

585
00:35:38,719 --> 00:35:40,054
Leave.

586
00:35:40,138 --> 00:35:42,473
You're ruining our reunion.

587
00:35:42,557 --> 00:35:49,397
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

588
00:35:55,153 --> 00:35:57,155
Hey, what are you doing?

589
00:36:08,624 --> 00:36:10,209
What did you do to Olivia, huh?!

590
00:36:10,293 --> 00:36:12,503
- [GRUNTS]
- Where's she?! Where's Olivia?!

591
00:36:12,587 --> 00:36:13,963
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

592
00:36:14,046 --> 00:36:16,632
[HUFFING]

593
00:36:16,716 --> 00:36:19,510
Juliana went back to Alex, Grandma?

594
00:36:24,223 --> 00:36:27,226
Why? After everything he has done to her?!

595
00:36:28,186 --> 00:36:30,354
I don't understand her either.

596
00:36:30,438 --> 00:36:32,356
I tried to convince her
several times last night

597
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:33,774
that she shouldn't do it.

598
00:36:33,858 --> 00:36:35,735
But she's desperate.

599
00:36:35,818 --> 00:36:37,778
Victor doesn't trust her anymore.

600
00:36:39,030 --> 00:36:41,949
She went with Alex because
she knew that he was the only one

601
00:36:42,033 --> 00:36:43,868
who could help her.

602
00:36:45,328 --> 00:36:46,913
Help?

603
00:36:46,996 --> 00:36:49,874
But, Grandma, she's only got herself
into something worse than prison.

604
00:36:49,957 --> 00:36:53,544
And I'm sure Alex will just grow
more possessive of her.

605
00:36:53,628 --> 00:36:55,004
You know,

606
00:36:57,131 --> 00:36:58,883
I'm worried about Abby.

607
00:37:00,176 --> 00:37:03,179
She'll definitely look for her mom.

608
00:37:03,262 --> 00:37:05,014
She'll ask about Juliana.

609
00:37:05,097 --> 00:37:07,141
What are we going to say to her?

610
00:37:11,187 --> 00:37:12,897
I'll take care of it, Grandma.

611
00:37:13,773 --> 00:37:20,696
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

612
00:37:28,496 --> 00:37:29,914
What are you talking about?!

613
00:37:29,997 --> 00:37:31,207
Do you see this, huh?!

614
00:37:31,290 --> 00:37:32,959
This is Olivia's ring!

615
00:37:33,042 --> 00:37:34,961
What did you do to her, huh?!

616
00:37:36,462 --> 00:37:37,838
All right!

617
00:37:37,922 --> 00:37:39,799
Fine! You've caught me!

618
00:37:39,882 --> 00:37:41,092
You're right!

619
00:37:41,926 --> 00:37:43,302
Olivia came here.

620
00:37:44,470 --> 00:37:46,222
But I didn't do anything to her.

621
00:37:47,098 --> 00:37:48,683
Although she did something to me.

622
00:37:49,934 --> 00:37:51,560
The two of us slept together.

623
00:37:51,644 --> 00:37:53,354
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

624
00:37:53,437 --> 00:37:55,231
[CHUCKLES]

625
00:37:55,314 --> 00:37:56,232
Bastard!

626
00:37:57,692 --> 00:38:01,654
- Alex! That's enough!
- Where is she, huh?!

627
00:38:01,737 --> 00:38:05,157
- Where?!
- Wait!

628
00:38:05,241 --> 00:38:07,618
Go on, punch me again!
You're just out on bail, right?!

629
00:38:07,702 --> 00:38:09,870
I'll send you back to jail
if you hit me again!

630
00:38:09,954 --> 00:38:11,289
Victor, stop it!

631
00:38:11,372 --> 00:38:13,749
[LAUGHING MANICALLY]

632
00:38:14,875 --> 00:38:16,294
[GRUNTS]

633
00:38:16,377 --> 00:38:17,920
I said enough!

634
00:38:18,671 --> 00:38:21,007
Fine, I'll let you hit me!

635
00:38:21,549 --> 00:38:22,675
I made a fool out of you!

636
00:38:23,050 --> 00:38:24,635
You got cheated on again!

637
00:38:25,803 --> 00:38:28,055
Olivia wouldn't do what you're saying!

638
00:38:28,139 --> 00:38:29,974
That's what I also thought, Victor!

639
00:38:30,057 --> 00:38:32,810
That's what I also thought!
But because of you…

640
00:38:32,893 --> 00:38:34,103
It's your fault!

641
00:38:34,186 --> 00:38:36,230
You kept approaching Juliana!

642
00:38:36,314 --> 00:38:38,149
That's why your wife came here

643
00:38:38,232 --> 00:38:39,942
to get back at the two of you!

644
00:38:40,318 --> 00:38:41,652
Who am I to say no?

645
00:38:42,778 --> 00:38:43,863
Who?!

646
00:38:43,946 --> 00:38:46,073
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

647
00:38:46,157 --> 00:38:47,908
Her idea of revenge is incredible.

648
00:38:49,076 --> 00:38:50,703
- What did you say?!
- Hey, hey, hey!

649
00:38:50,786 --> 00:38:53,539
Victor, wait, wait, wait.
You still don't believe me?

650
00:38:54,081 --> 00:38:55,708
Huh? Here.

651
00:38:59,920 --> 00:39:00,921
[ALEX CHUCKLES]

652
00:39:01,005 --> 00:39:02,923
ARE YOU FREE TONIGHT, ALEX?
I JUST NEED TO TALK.

653
00:39:03,007 --> 00:39:04,550
HE'S MY PROBLEM. HIM AND JULIANA.

654
00:39:04,633 --> 00:39:06,010
I THINK THEY'RE GETTING
BACK TOGETHER.

655
00:39:06,093 --> 00:39:08,387
I WANT TO TAKE REVENGE, ALEX.
LET'S GET BACK AT THEM.

656
00:39:08,471 --> 00:39:10,890
There are more messages
if you want to read more.

657
00:39:12,975 --> 00:39:14,060
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

658
00:39:14,143 --> 00:39:16,645
She left immediately after we did it.

659
00:39:16,729 --> 00:39:18,773
She said she didn't want to
see you again. I mean…

660
00:39:19,315 --> 00:39:22,193
she thinks you and Juliana
are still together.

661
00:39:22,943 --> 00:39:25,071
So she left you.

662
00:39:26,906 --> 00:39:28,240
[CHUCKLES]

663
00:39:32,203 --> 00:39:33,371
Now leave!

664
00:39:33,454 --> 00:39:40,461
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

665
00:39:42,213 --> 00:39:43,297
[ALEX] Get out!

666
00:39:55,684 --> 00:39:57,770
How did Victor see the ring?

667
00:39:58,646 --> 00:40:00,731
Why are you asking me?

668
00:40:00,815 --> 00:40:02,733
Didn't something happen
between you and Olivia?

669
00:40:02,817 --> 00:40:04,944
Maybe it fell during that.

670
00:40:05,027 --> 00:40:07,863
Yes, I admit, I made a mistake.

671
00:40:07,947 --> 00:40:09,156
Yes.

672
00:40:09,240 --> 00:40:10,491
But you left me.

673
00:40:11,742 --> 00:40:13,244
Can you blame me?

674
00:40:13,744 --> 00:40:15,162
It didn't mean anything.

675
00:40:16,997 --> 00:40:19,792
Olivia and I wanted the same thing.

676
00:40:19,875 --> 00:40:22,128
To get back at you and Victor.

677
00:40:23,337 --> 00:40:25,881
Victor and I aren't together, Alex.

678
00:40:25,965 --> 00:40:28,259
Nothing happened.

679
00:40:28,342 --> 00:40:29,927
I wouldn't betray you.

680
00:40:30,553 --> 00:40:31,637
But you?

681
00:40:32,555 --> 00:40:34,432
What else am I expecting?

682
00:40:34,515 --> 00:40:36,308
Olivia came here.

683
00:40:37,476 --> 00:40:38,894
She seduced me.

684
00:40:41,063 --> 00:40:42,731
I know you, Alex.

685
00:40:42,815 --> 00:40:44,400
Whether you admit it or not,

686
00:40:44,817 --> 00:40:47,361
you want everything Victor has,

687
00:40:47,445 --> 00:40:49,989
including everyone who loves him.

688
00:40:50,072 --> 00:40:52,283
Me before, and now Olivia too?

689
00:40:52,366 --> 00:40:53,576
That's not true!

690
00:40:54,243 --> 00:40:56,954
Will you replace me
the way you replaced Sylvia?

691
00:40:57,037 --> 00:40:57,913
No.

692
00:40:57,997 --> 00:41:00,249
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

693
00:41:00,332 --> 00:41:01,750
No. Stay here.

694
00:41:02,918 --> 00:41:04,170
No.

695
00:41:06,005 --> 00:41:07,131
No.

696
00:41:09,341 --> 00:41:10,968
I'm sorry.

697
00:41:11,051 --> 00:41:13,387
I'm sorry for what I did, please.

698
00:41:13,471 --> 00:41:15,973
But believe me,
I won't replace you with Olivia.

699
00:41:16,056 --> 00:41:18,476
She's nothing compared to you.

700
00:41:18,559 --> 00:41:20,102
I love you, Liana.

701
00:41:20,561 --> 00:41:22,021
You are the only one I love.

702
00:41:24,732 --> 00:41:26,775
I'm just scared, Alex.

703
00:41:28,694 --> 00:41:30,529
That you might hurt me again.

704
00:41:32,364 --> 00:41:34,366
You know how much I love you.

705
00:41:35,493 --> 00:41:38,204
But you've broken my trust so many times.

706
00:41:38,287 --> 00:41:42,917
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

707
00:41:43,000 --> 00:41:44,627
That won't happen again.

708
00:41:45,628 --> 00:41:47,004
Believe me.

709
00:41:47,087 --> 00:41:48,714
We'll start over again.

710
00:41:49,507 --> 00:41:52,259
We've both made mistakes.
Can we forgive each other?

711
00:41:52,343 --> 00:41:59,308
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

712
00:42:18,744 --> 00:42:25,751
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

713
00:42:40,599 --> 00:42:47,773
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

714
00:43:01,787 --> 00:43:03,664
[MATTEO] Olivia's ring.

715
00:43:04,873 --> 00:43:06,417
How did he see it?

716
00:43:07,334 --> 00:43:09,378
I don't know. Maybe it fell when she ran.

717
00:43:09,461 --> 00:43:10,921
Fortunately, I dealt with it.

718
00:43:11,755 --> 00:43:13,591
If only you'd seen Victor's face

719
00:43:13,674 --> 00:43:15,968
when I said something happened
between Olivia and me.

720
00:43:16,051 --> 00:43:18,345
Do you think he'd believe that?

721
00:43:19,513 --> 00:43:21,682
He'll still look for Olivia.

722
00:43:22,683 --> 00:43:24,101
If anything, you're in deeper trouble

723
00:43:24,184 --> 00:43:26,562
since you were the last person with her.

724
00:43:28,022 --> 00:43:29,273
You're right.

725
00:43:29,356 --> 00:43:31,525
We need to tie up all loose ends.

726
00:43:32,693 --> 00:43:33,902
[ALEX] Come on.

727
00:43:35,070 --> 00:43:36,864
- Where?
- To your office.

728
00:43:40,075 --> 00:43:41,744
Oh, you're leaving?

729
00:43:42,494 --> 00:43:44,496
Matteo and I
need to take care of something.

730
00:43:45,331 --> 00:43:47,041
We're reviewing Victor's contract.

731
00:43:47,124 --> 00:43:48,542
I'm leaving the company.

732
00:43:49,960 --> 00:43:51,962
Okay. Don't stay out too late.

733
00:43:52,671 --> 00:43:54,214
I'll walk you out.

734
00:43:57,968 --> 00:44:01,597
Ma'am, my wife went missing
the other night.

735
00:44:02,306 --> 00:44:07,853
The admin said you own
the vacant lot used for parking

736
00:44:07,936 --> 00:44:11,106
near my brother
Alexander Lualhati's house.

737
00:44:12,483 --> 00:44:15,569
Can I see your CCTV footage?

738
00:44:16,320 --> 00:44:17,905
You're Victor, right?

739
00:44:17,988 --> 00:44:20,074
The one who was imprisoned
for Sylvia's death?

740
00:44:20,824 --> 00:44:22,660
I wasn't convicted.

741
00:44:22,743 --> 00:44:23,994
I'm innocent.

742
00:44:24,078 --> 00:44:26,580
Are you really not at fault?

743
00:44:26,664 --> 00:44:28,374
Ma'am, if I were guilty,

744
00:44:28,457 --> 00:44:30,501
I would've gone into hiding
after posting bail.

745
00:44:30,584 --> 00:44:34,213
Please, ma'am, can I view your footage?

746
00:44:37,549 --> 00:44:41,720
Sir, could I see the CCTV footage
from the other night?

747
00:44:41,804 --> 00:44:44,181
Ask the police, not us.

748
00:44:44,264 --> 00:44:45,349
You're bothering us.

749
00:44:45,724 --> 00:44:49,103
We don't let strangers in here.

750
00:44:49,186 --> 00:44:50,270
What are you waiting for?

751
00:44:50,938 --> 00:44:52,189
You can leave now.

752
00:44:52,272 --> 00:44:54,400
S-Sir, maybe…

753
00:44:54,483 --> 00:44:57,152
Mary Anne, make sure to lock
the gate securely, okay?

754
00:44:57,236 --> 00:44:58,654
When I leave, don't wait for me.

755
00:44:58,737 --> 00:45:00,406
- Okay.
- I'll be home late.

756
00:45:00,489 --> 00:45:01,573
All right.

757
00:45:03,992 --> 00:45:08,914
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

758
00:45:10,833 --> 00:45:12,543
[CAR STARTS]

759
00:45:17,423 --> 00:45:20,050
Ma'am, ma'am, I'm begging you.

760
00:45:20,134 --> 00:45:22,010
I'm really worried about my wife.

761
00:45:24,304 --> 00:45:27,891
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

762
00:45:27,975 --> 00:45:29,810
Text me when you're on the way home, okay?

763
00:45:29,893 --> 00:45:31,437
- All right.
- Okay.

764
00:45:35,232 --> 00:45:36,900
Drive safely.

765
00:45:36,984 --> 00:45:38,193
[ALEX] Thank you.

766
00:45:55,002 --> 00:45:56,879
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

767
00:45:56,962 --> 00:45:58,172
Abby?

768
00:45:58,839 --> 00:46:01,758
What are you doing here?
Does your dad know about this?

769
00:46:01,842 --> 00:46:02,926
What about Grandma Pilar?

770
00:46:03,343 --> 00:46:05,762
Why did you go back to Uncle Alex?

771
00:46:08,307 --> 00:46:10,767
Come with me, Mommy.

772
00:46:10,851 --> 00:46:12,936
Let's go home to Dad.

773
00:46:13,020 --> 00:46:15,397
- Let's go.
- Abby, stop.

774
00:46:15,481 --> 00:46:17,608
Uncle Alex and I have patched things up.

775
00:46:17,691 --> 00:46:19,693
He won't hurt me anymore. He's changed.

776
00:46:20,068 --> 00:46:22,029
If he hurts you again,

777
00:46:22,112 --> 00:46:23,238
who will protect you?

778
00:46:23,322 --> 00:46:25,574
Abby, trust me.

779
00:46:26,116 --> 00:46:28,202
I can take care of myself.

780
00:46:28,285 --> 00:46:30,996
Just go home. Go on.

781
00:46:32,080 --> 00:46:34,166
If you don't want to come with me,

782
00:46:34,249 --> 00:46:36,418
I'll stay with you.

783
00:46:36,502 --> 00:46:38,420
I won't leave you here, Mommy.

784
00:46:38,504 --> 00:46:41,006
Why are you so stubborn, Abby?!

785
00:46:41,089 --> 00:46:43,759
I told you to leave, didn't I?!

786
00:46:43,842 --> 00:46:45,135
Go home.

787
00:46:45,969 --> 00:46:48,388
You'll just make things harder for me
if you stay here.

788
00:46:48,847 --> 00:46:51,767
I won't be a burden, Mommy, please.

789
00:46:51,850 --> 00:46:53,560
Your father needs you more.

790
00:46:53,644 --> 00:46:55,812
I need you both!

791
00:46:59,483 --> 00:47:01,360
[LINE RINGING]

792
00:47:01,443 --> 00:47:02,528
Hello, Grandma?

793
00:47:03,195 --> 00:47:05,072
Abby is here.

794
00:47:07,241 --> 00:47:08,992
We're here at Alex's.

795
00:47:23,215 --> 00:47:26,426
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

796
00:47:34,560 --> 00:47:35,644
Olivia.

797
00:47:41,650 --> 00:47:42,859
Alex?

798
00:47:42,943 --> 00:47:45,529
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

799
00:47:45,612 --> 00:47:47,364
Is she the one you're looking for?

800
00:47:48,574 --> 00:47:50,784
You should report this to the police.

801
00:47:54,079 --> 00:47:55,414
It's not enough.

802
00:47:56,123 --> 00:47:57,249
I know my brother.

803
00:47:57,332 --> 00:47:59,209
He'll get away with it.

804
00:47:59,293 --> 00:48:01,086
He can turn it all around.

805
00:48:01,169 --> 00:48:03,338
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

806
00:48:03,422 --> 00:48:05,507
I need more solid evidence.

807
00:48:07,884 --> 00:48:10,679
Wait for me in the cab.
I'll be right there.

808
00:48:12,889 --> 00:48:13,932
Mommy.

809
00:48:14,266 --> 00:48:16,226
Abby, stop being stubborn.

810
00:48:16,310 --> 00:48:17,311
Go on.

811
00:48:21,273 --> 00:48:22,482
Abby.

812
00:48:30,365 --> 00:48:31,825
Be careful.

813
00:48:32,951 --> 00:48:34,369
I love you so much.

814
00:48:35,412 --> 00:48:37,164
Don't forget that, okay?

815
00:48:39,166 --> 00:48:40,292
Go on.

816
00:48:52,638 --> 00:48:54,640
You're really pushing your daughter away?

817
00:48:55,432 --> 00:48:58,060
Grandma, I don't want to
argue with you anymore.

818
00:48:58,143 --> 00:49:00,062
Please take care of Abby.

819
00:49:00,145 --> 00:49:02,439
Keep an eye on her
so she can't come back here.

820
00:49:03,482 --> 00:49:04,941
I don't know

821
00:49:05,025 --> 00:49:07,277
what's running through your mind, Juliana.

822
00:49:07,778 --> 00:49:09,696
You know, if violence wasn't bad,

823
00:49:09,780 --> 00:49:11,907
I'd pull all your hair out

824
00:49:11,990 --> 00:49:14,117
and knock some sense into you!

825
00:49:15,869 --> 00:49:17,537
You're really choosing to be with Alex,

826
00:49:17,621 --> 00:49:20,248
that vile husband of yours,
ahead of your daughter?!

827
00:49:20,332 --> 00:49:23,043
What were you thinking,
going back to him?!

828
00:49:23,126 --> 00:49:24,878
What if he hurts you again?!

829
00:49:25,671 --> 00:49:27,506
Grandma, Alex won't do that anymore.

830
00:49:28,256 --> 00:49:30,717
- He promised me.
- And you believed him?!

831
00:49:30,801 --> 00:49:33,011
We should give him the chance to change.

832
00:49:33,095 --> 00:49:35,055
From what I've seen…

833
00:49:36,139 --> 00:49:38,517
I think he means it.

834
00:49:38,600 --> 00:49:41,269
I want to fix my marriage.

835
00:49:41,353 --> 00:49:44,064
Or is it because you just
don't want to be separated again?

836
00:49:44,147 --> 00:49:46,817
What kind of reasoning is that?

837
00:49:48,068 --> 00:49:50,821
The way you look at love
is really distorted!

838
00:49:51,279 --> 00:49:54,449
You easily left a decent man like Victor,

839
00:49:54,533 --> 00:49:57,452
but you're chasing
that demon Alex around like a dog

840
00:49:57,536 --> 00:50:00,580
even though he abuses you!

841
00:50:00,664 --> 00:50:02,124
What's wrong with you?!

842
00:50:02,833 --> 00:50:05,293
You have a choice, Juliana.

843
00:50:05,919 --> 00:50:09,548
But I don't know why
you're choosing to do this!

844
00:50:09,631 --> 00:50:11,425
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

845
00:50:11,508 --> 00:50:14,052
You don't need to
lock yourself up in here.

846
00:50:15,178 --> 00:50:19,015
You'll understand
why I'm doing all of this someday.

847
00:50:22,352 --> 00:50:24,771
It's for the good of everyone, Grandma.

848
00:50:24,855 --> 00:50:26,898
Whatever it is you're planning,

849
00:50:28,817 --> 00:50:30,652
I hope you don't get hurt.

850
00:50:32,362 --> 00:50:33,613
Remember,

851
00:50:33,697 --> 00:50:36,074
all the people who were close to Alex…

852
00:50:37,242 --> 00:50:39,119
met tragic ends.

853
00:50:39,745 --> 00:50:41,830
You should get going, Grandma.

854
00:50:41,913 --> 00:50:43,415
Abby is waiting.

855
00:50:43,498 --> 00:50:45,125
Take care of her for me.

856
00:50:46,209 --> 00:50:47,294
Go on.

857
00:50:47,377 --> 00:50:54,426
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

858
00:50:55,427 --> 00:50:56,595
Bye, Grandma.

859
00:51:03,769 --> 00:51:04,811
[CAR DOOR CLOSES]

860
00:51:04,895 --> 00:51:07,314
[ENGINE REVVING]

861
00:51:08,982 --> 00:51:15,947
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

862
00:51:21,995 --> 00:51:29,002
[SOBBING]

863
00:51:36,218 --> 00:51:38,553
Here is a copy of the footage.

864
00:51:38,637 --> 00:51:40,305
I hope you find your wife.

865
00:51:40,388 --> 00:51:42,224
Thank you so much for your help.

866
00:51:42,599 --> 00:51:45,268
It's the least I can do for you.

867
00:51:45,352 --> 00:51:47,062
The truth is,

868
00:51:47,145 --> 00:51:49,272
I was going to ask for another favor.

869
00:51:49,648 --> 00:51:50,857
What's that?

870
00:51:52,275 --> 00:51:54,319
The night Sylvia died,

871
00:51:55,153 --> 00:51:58,323
I have a video of my ex-wife
coming out of the house.

872
00:51:58,824 --> 00:52:02,577
There's CCTV footage of her arriving
at my brother's house that night.

873
00:52:03,203 --> 00:52:05,872
The angle of the CCTV
matches the one on your property,

874
00:52:05,956 --> 00:52:08,333
but the content on this is different.

875
00:52:10,377 --> 00:52:12,504
Can I see a copy of that?

876
00:52:13,004 --> 00:52:14,798
Can I see that

877
00:52:15,715 --> 00:52:17,592
CCTV footage?

878
00:52:19,094 --> 00:52:21,137
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

879
00:52:21,221 --> 00:52:26,226
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

880
00:52:36,987 --> 00:52:43,994
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

881
00:52:59,009 --> 00:53:05,390
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

882
00:53:08,852 --> 00:53:11,271
Everything that Liana said was true.

883
00:53:11,938 --> 00:53:15,025
Ma'am, is there any more footage
from this CCTV?

884
00:53:16,610 --> 00:53:18,403
No. That's all.

885
00:53:19,195 --> 00:53:20,488
[EXHALES SOFTLY]

886
00:53:20,572 --> 00:53:23,241
[MARY ANNE] To be honest,
my husband deleted it.

887
00:53:23,325 --> 00:53:25,619
He told the police that

888
00:53:26,411 --> 00:53:28,914
our CCTV was faulty that day.

889
00:53:29,789 --> 00:53:32,459
I got about curious why he needed to lie,

890
00:53:32,542 --> 00:53:37,088
so I looked into where
the CCTV files were.

891
00:53:38,089 --> 00:53:40,050
But that's all I managed to recover.

892
00:53:41,635 --> 00:53:44,679
However, I found something else
from another camera.

893
00:53:44,763 --> 00:53:51,686
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

894
00:54:02,781 --> 00:54:04,574
<i>Alex was at home.</i>

895
00:54:05,659 --> 00:54:08,453
<i>He was there when Sylvia died.</i>

896
00:54:08,536 --> 00:54:10,830
<i>He was already there before Juliana.</i>

897
00:54:11,581 --> 00:54:13,124
<i>Before I arrived.</i>

898
00:54:13,208 --> 00:54:20,215
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

899
00:54:23,009 --> 00:54:24,219
Ma'am, thank you.

900
00:54:26,388 --> 00:54:27,973
Thank you for your help.

901
00:54:30,642 --> 00:54:32,769
I know it's hard for you,

902
00:54:33,645 --> 00:54:35,981
doing this even though
you're scared of your husband.

903
00:54:36,856 --> 00:54:39,651
I wanted to turn this over to the cops.

904
00:54:39,734 --> 00:54:41,820
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

905
00:54:41,903 --> 00:54:44,823
I kept thinking about doing
the right thing.

906
00:54:46,324 --> 00:54:47,742
But I got scared.

907
00:54:48,535 --> 00:54:50,245
Our business was going bankrupt

908
00:54:50,328 --> 00:54:52,664
and we were in danger of losing our house.

909
00:54:53,915 --> 00:54:56,292
But after Sylvia died,

910
00:54:57,502 --> 00:55:00,422
I saw them talking to Alex's lawyer.

911
00:55:01,006 --> 00:55:02,215
After that…

912
00:55:04,009 --> 00:55:06,636
all our debts were paid off. [CRIES]

913
00:55:07,470 --> 00:55:10,306
A lot of money came into
the business. [CRYING]

914
00:55:12,892 --> 00:55:15,186
Then I heard

915
00:55:15,270 --> 00:55:17,814
you'd been jailed for Sylvia's murder.

916
00:55:17,897 --> 00:55:21,151
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

917
00:55:21,234 --> 00:55:23,903
After my husband got that money,

918
00:55:23,987 --> 00:55:25,989
he changed.

919
00:55:26,072 --> 00:55:33,329
He got involved with women
and got addicted to vices.

920
00:55:36,541 --> 00:55:38,918
Our marriage fell apart.

921
00:55:40,003 --> 00:55:41,463
[CAR HORN BLARING]

922
00:55:44,257 --> 00:55:46,843
My husband is back. You need to leave now.

923
00:55:46,926 --> 00:55:47,969
Use the back door.

924
00:55:48,053 --> 00:55:49,345
Ma'am, thank you very much.

925
00:55:49,429 --> 00:55:50,847
Come on, hurry up.

926
00:55:55,268 --> 00:55:56,269
[DOOR CLOSES]

927
00:56:03,151 --> 00:56:05,028
What are you doing here?

928
00:56:05,111 --> 00:56:07,030
Are you really looking for trouble?

929
00:56:07,655 --> 00:56:09,741
I'm looking for answers, Juliana,

930
00:56:09,824 --> 00:56:11,201
not trouble.

931
00:56:12,160 --> 00:56:13,703
[CHUCKLES WRYLY] Why?

932
00:56:14,412 --> 00:56:16,081
Will you believe me?

933
00:56:16,956 --> 00:56:18,041
No, right?

934
00:56:18,124 --> 00:56:20,794
Because you think I'm a liar.

935
00:56:21,169 --> 00:56:23,630
Well, Victor, you've got the wrong person.

936
00:56:24,297 --> 00:56:27,717
So, you'd better leave
before Alex catches you.

937
00:56:27,801 --> 00:56:29,677
I'm not scared of Alex.

938
00:56:29,761 --> 00:56:31,012
Victor, leave now!

939
00:56:31,096 --> 00:56:33,181
Juliana, why did you come back here?

940
00:56:36,559 --> 00:56:38,394
Because Alex is my husband, Victor.

941
00:56:39,854 --> 00:56:42,232
Of course I would come back.

942
00:56:42,315 --> 00:56:45,318
I won't allow my family
to be destroyed again.

943
00:56:45,985 --> 00:56:47,112
Family?

944
00:56:48,446 --> 00:56:50,156
Isn't Abby family to you?

945
00:56:51,241 --> 00:56:52,951
Why didn't you bring her here?

946
00:56:54,536 --> 00:56:56,037
I know you, Juliana.

947
00:56:56,121 --> 00:56:59,040
You wouldn't just leave
our child like that.

948
00:57:03,044 --> 00:57:04,504
So answer me…

949
00:57:05,922 --> 00:57:07,674
Why did you come back here?

950
00:57:09,050 --> 00:57:11,469
If you like what's happening to you now…

951
00:57:13,012 --> 00:57:14,472
why are you crying?

952
00:57:26,151 --> 00:57:27,944
Are you the reason I saw this?

953
00:57:28,027 --> 00:57:35,243
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

954
00:57:43,418 --> 00:57:44,711
[VICTOR]<i> Alex!</i>

955
00:57:46,421 --> 00:57:47,547
<i>Who's that?</i>

956
00:57:48,256 --> 00:57:50,133
<i>- It's Victor.</i>
<i>- Victor?</i>

957
00:57:50,216 --> 00:57:57,223
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

958
00:57:58,308 --> 00:57:59,601
[RING CLATTERS]

959
00:58:12,197 --> 00:58:15,450
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

960
00:58:15,533 --> 00:58:17,243
Answer me, Juliana.

961
00:58:26,252 --> 00:58:27,378
[SNIFFLES]

962
00:58:32,800 --> 00:58:34,427
What are you planning to do?

963
00:58:34,511 --> 00:58:41,851
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

964
00:58:41,935 --> 00:58:43,728
Juliana, forgive me…

965
00:58:46,147 --> 00:58:47,941
for doubting you.

966
00:58:50,944 --> 00:58:54,489
I now know that everything you told me

967
00:58:54,572 --> 00:58:56,574
about the night Sylvia died was true.

968
00:59:01,079 --> 00:59:02,413
How?

969
00:59:03,039 --> 00:59:06,292
I found the rest of the video
that Dante showed us.

970
00:59:08,253 --> 00:59:10,338
Alex had hidden it for a long time.

971
00:59:11,506 --> 00:59:13,299
And you were right.

972
00:59:13,383 --> 00:59:14,842
They'd edited it.

973
00:59:15,760 --> 00:59:17,971
They did it on purpose to frame you.

974
00:59:18,054 --> 00:59:21,140
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

975
00:59:21,224 --> 00:59:23,101
And that's not all I found out.

976
00:59:25,853 --> 00:59:26,938
What?

977
00:59:27,647 --> 00:59:29,566
The night Olivia disappeared…

978
00:59:31,776 --> 00:59:33,653
Juliana, she was running from here.

979
00:59:33,736 --> 00:59:35,863
Alex was chasing her.

980
00:59:38,575 --> 00:59:40,785
So answer me, Juliana…

981
00:59:40,868 --> 00:59:42,161
Why did you come back here?

982
00:59:42,245 --> 00:59:44,497
Because I want to know the truth.

983
00:59:46,332 --> 00:59:48,918
Because I want to help you, Victor.

984
00:59:49,919 --> 00:59:56,926
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

985
00:59:57,802 --> 01:00:01,222
I came back to correct my mistake.

986
01:00:04,350 --> 01:00:07,395
I want to make Alex pay
for what he did wrong.

987
01:00:07,937 --> 01:00:10,481
I want to clear our names.

988
01:00:10,565 --> 01:00:11,899
Especially yours.

989
01:00:14,110 --> 01:00:17,155
I won't allow Alex
to hurt anyone else again.

990
01:00:18,197 --> 01:00:21,326
So if I have to stay away from
my daughter for now,

991
01:00:22,160 --> 01:00:24,037
I can endure it.

992
01:00:31,836 --> 01:00:34,339
Liana, you don't have to do this.

993
01:00:34,422 --> 01:00:36,924
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

994
01:00:37,008 --> 01:00:38,092
Alex is hurting you.

995
01:00:38,176 --> 01:00:40,345
Are you really going to wait
for it to get worse?

996
01:00:40,428 --> 01:00:43,181
I'm the only one
who can get close to Alex.

997
01:00:43,264 --> 01:00:45,808
I can't just sit here, Victor.

998
01:00:45,892 --> 01:00:48,269
So don't worry about me. Just let me be.

999
01:00:48,936 --> 01:00:51,731
Because I'm the one who started all this.

1000
01:00:52,857 --> 01:00:55,360
None of this would've happened if…

1001
01:00:57,570 --> 01:00:59,447
if I hadn't cheated on you before.

1002
01:00:59,530 --> 01:01:02,742
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

1003
01:01:02,825 --> 01:01:05,286
So forgive me, Victor. [CRYING]

1004
01:01:05,370 --> 01:01:07,330
Even Olivia got dragged into this.

1005
01:01:07,705 --> 01:01:08,831
We know Alex.

1006
01:01:08,915 --> 01:01:11,834
He won't stop until he hurts us all.

1007
01:01:14,170 --> 01:01:15,421
[CRYING]

1008
01:01:15,505 --> 01:01:17,298
Forgive me.

1009
01:01:18,758 --> 01:01:20,760
[CRYING]

1010
01:01:20,843 --> 01:01:21,969
Stop crying.

1011
01:01:22,053 --> 01:01:27,433
[CRYING]

1012
01:01:27,517 --> 01:01:28,559
That's enough.

1013
01:01:28,643 --> 01:01:35,650
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

1014
01:01:36,442 --> 01:01:37,860
Stop crying, Juliana.

1015
01:01:39,612 --> 01:01:41,280
I promise you,

1016
01:01:42,407 --> 01:01:44,534
I'll help you as much as I can.

1017
01:01:45,785 --> 01:01:48,746
I heard Alex and Matteo talking.

1018
01:01:51,290 --> 01:01:52,667
What did they say?

1019
01:01:53,376 --> 01:01:55,002
They said they were afraid that

1020
01:01:55,878 --> 01:01:58,589
you wouldn't stop looking for Olivia.

1021
01:01:58,923 --> 01:02:05,638
[PHONE RINGING]

1022
01:02:07,265 --> 01:02:08,391
It's Olivia.

1023
01:02:09,934 --> 01:02:12,895
[RINGING CONTINUES]

1024
01:02:13,771 --> 01:02:14,689
Liv?

1025
01:02:14,772 --> 01:02:16,107
Liv, where are you?

1026
01:02:16,816 --> 01:02:18,568
- Liv?
- [BUSY TONE]

1027
01:02:18,651 --> 01:02:19,736
Liv!

1028
01:02:22,572 --> 01:02:26,242
- [BREATH QUIVERING]
- [LINE RINGING]

1029
01:02:26,325 --> 01:02:28,411
[BUSY TONE]

1030
01:02:28,494 --> 01:02:32,582
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

1031
01:02:32,665 --> 01:02:33,750
[BUSY TONE]

1032
01:02:33,833 --> 01:02:34,959
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

1033
01:02:37,044 --> 01:02:38,087
[PHONE CHIMES]

1034
01:02:43,092 --> 01:02:44,260
SORRY I LEFT WITHOUT A WORD.

1035
01:02:44,343 --> 01:02:46,053
I WAS DEEPLY HURT BY WHAT
YOU AND JULIANA DID.

1036
01:02:46,137 --> 01:02:48,055
I NEED TIME TO HEAL.
DON'T LOOK FOR ME. I'M SAFE.

1037
01:02:48,139 --> 01:02:55,354
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]
